<subSubSection id="E9C66514075DFFC51013071EFE3CAEB4" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" type="description">
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC61013071EFC25AA09" blockId="37.[811,1458,1300,1804]" box="[813,957,1300,1326]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC61013073EFC15AA6B" blockId="37.[811,1458,1300,1804]" box="[813,909,1332,1358]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075DFFC61013073EFC15AA6B" box="[813,909,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Carapace</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC610130759FBA3A829" blockId="37.[811,1458,1300,1804]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Sub-cylindrical carapace; fusiform intercalated plate; narrow post-orbital area; wide cephalic region; deep and wide cervical groove, strongly inclined, joined to dorsal margin and to antennal groove; deep and narrow antennal groove; short, shallow gastro-orbital groove, oblique, originating as a slight median inflexion of cervical groove; inferior gastro-orbital lobe slightly inflated; postcervical and branchiocardiac grooves subparallel; deep postcervical groove, strongly inclined and curved forward, joined to dorsal margin and interrupted in hepatic region; deep branchiocardiac groove, slightly curved forward, joined to dorsal margin and to hepatic groove; hepatic groove concavo-convex, joined to cervical groove; ω and χ areas slightly inflated; deep, wide inferior groove, joined to hepatic groove.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC61013053BFC73A86E" blockId="37.[813,1003,1841,1867]" box="[813,1003,1841,1867]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">
<heading id="FA2B81F3075DFFC61013053BFC73A86E" box="[813,1003,1841,1867]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" reason="8">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075DFFC61013053BFC73A86E" box="[813,1003,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Pleon and uropods</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC61013055BFB90A8AE" blockId="37.[813,1454,1873,1932]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Somites with subtriangular pleurites, with a longitudinal bulge on their basis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC6101305BBFC66A8EE" blockId="37.[813,1022,1969,1995]" box="[813,1022,1969,1995]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">
<heading id="FA2B81F3075DFFC6101305BBFC66A8EE" box="[813,1022,1969,1995]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="37" pageNumber="60" reason="8">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075DFFC6101305BBFC66A8EE" box="[813,1022,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Thoracic appendages</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075DFFC6101305DBFBADA8C9" blockId="37.[813,1077,2001,2028]" box="[813,1077,2001,2028]" pageId="37" pageNumber="60">Elongated P2-P5 merus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA02D2FEBEAFD7" blockId="38.[132,294,216,242]" box="[132,294,216,242]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="FA2B81F3075EFFC513BA02D2FEBEAFD7" box="[132,294,216,242]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" reason="8">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513BA02D2FEBEAFD7" box="[132,294,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Ornamentation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA02FDFE3CAEB4" blockId="38.[132,777,247,401]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Carapace densely covered by small tubercles preceded by depressions, the tubercles are coarser along the intercalated plate; pleonal somites densely covered by small rounded depressions; P2-P5 merus covered by small rounded and widely spaced depressions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9C66514075EFFC513BA03BDFEA9AB8B" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA03BDFE9EAEEA" blockId="38.[130,777,439,1198]" box="[132,262,439,465]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">DISCUSSION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513BA03DCFEC0AC8A" blockId="38.[130,777,439,1198]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
This species was described from a carapace firstly assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC513BA03FDFEE1AD34" authority="(Secretan 1964)" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[132,377,502,529]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513BA03FDFF50AD35" box="[132,200,503,528]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Eryma</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075EFFC513E903FCFEF6AD35" author="SECRETAN S." box="[215,366,502,528]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 226" refId="ref35606" refString="SECRETAN S. 1964. - Les Crustaces decapodes du Jurassique superieur et du Cretace de Madagascar. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Nouvelle serie, Serie C, Sciences de la Terre 14: 1 - 226. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 58227347" type="journal article" year="1964">Secrétan 1964</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. A second species, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5110503FDFEBEAD15" authority="Secretan, 1964" authorityName="Secretan" authorityYear="1964" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5110503FDFC9DAD35" box="[571,773,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">E. madagascariensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075EFFC513BA001CFEBEAD15" author="SECRETAN S." box="[132,294,534,560]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 226" refId="ref35606" refString="SECRETAN S. 1964. - Les Crustaces decapodes du Jurassique superieur et du Cretace de Madagascar. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Nouvelle serie, Serie C, Sciences de la Terre 14: 1 - 226. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 58227347" type="journal article" year="1964">Secrétan, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a carapace connected to a fragment of pleon was also described (
<figureCitation id="39E72A1A075EFFC51293003CFD9BAD74" box="[429,515,566,593]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="35.[132,143,1962,1979]" captionTargetBox="[133,1455,215,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-28@36.[698,1267,768,1324]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIG. 16. — Stenodactylina insignis (Oppel,1862), Stenodactylina shotoverigiganti n. sp. and Stenodactylina granulifera (Secrétan,1964):A, holotype of S. insignis (Oxfordian, Haute-Saône, France); B, holotype MFN 2236 P1383/2 MB.A.1536 of Eryma anisodactylus Krause,1891 (Kimmeridgian, Holzen,Germany); C, specimen IRSNB without number of S. insignis (Kimmeridgian, La Rochelle, France); D-G, holotype NHMUK 24559 of S. shotoverigiganti n. sp. (Oxfordian, Shotover, United Kingdom):right lateral view (D), left lateral view (E), schema (F), dorsal view (G); H-J, holotype MNHN.F.R03975 of S. granulifera (Kimmeridgian,Antsalova, Madagascar): lateral view (H), schema (J); C, D, holotype MNHN.F.R03974 of Eryma madagascariensis Secrétan, 1964 (Kimmeridgian, Antsalova, Madagascar). Abbreviations:a, branchiocardiac groove;b, antennal groove; b1, hepatic groove; c, postcervical groove; d, gastro-orbital groove; e1e, cervical groove; i, inferior groove;ip, intercalated plate; χ, attachment site of adductor testis muscle;ω, attachment site of mandibular muscle.Photographs:A, L. Cazes;B-E, G,J. Devillez; H, J, C. Lemzaouda. Line drawings: J. Devillez. Scale bars: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4498594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4498594/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Fig. 16J</figureCitation>
). The review of the decapod crustaceans of 
<collectingCountry id="D9CB760F075EFFC51275005CFE51AD55" box="[331,457,598,624]" name="Madagascar" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075EFFC512D5005CFC9FAD55" author="CHARBONNIER S. &amp; GARASSINO A. &amp; PASINI G." box="[491,775,598,624]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" pagination="313 - 357" refId="ref30618" refString="CHARBONNIER S., GARASSINO A. &amp; PASINI G. 2012 a. - Revision of Mesozoic decapod crustaceans from Madagascar. Geodiversitas 34 (2): 313 - 357. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / g 2012 n 2 a 5" type="journal article" year="2012">
Charbonnier 
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51142005DFD36AD55" box="[636,686,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
(2012a)
</bibRefCitation>
concluded to the synonymy between 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51137007DFD40ADB5" authorityName="Secretan" authorityYear="1964" box="[521,728,630,656]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granuliferum">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51137007DFD40ADB5" box="[521,728,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Eryma granuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC513BC009CFED2AD95" authorityName="Secretan" authorityYear="1964" box="[130,330,662,688]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513BC009CFED2AD95" box="[130,330,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">E. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of their very close carapace groove pattern. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075EFFC5122600BFFE77ADF5" author="DEVILLEZ J. &amp; CHARBONNIER S. &amp; HYZNY M. &amp; LEROY L." box="[280,495,693,720]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" pagination="515 - 541" refId="ref31314" refString="DEVILLEZ J., CHARBONNIER S., HYZNY M. &amp; LEROY L. 2016. - Review of the Early Cretaceous erymid lobsters (Crustacea: Decapoda) from the Western Tethys. Geodiversitas 38 (4): 515 - 541. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / g 2016 n 4 a 4" type="journal article" year="2016">
Devillez 
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5124A00BCFE3CADEA" box="[372,420,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
assigned 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5117300BCFD73ADEA" authorityName="Secretan" authorityYear="1964" box="[589,747,693,719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granuliferum">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5117300BCFD73ADEA" box="[589,747,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">E. granuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC513BC00DFFE8FADCA" authorityName="Beurlen" authorityYear="1928" box="[130,279,725,751]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513BC00DFFE8FADCA" box="[130,279,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Stenodactylina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the absence of junction between the postcervical and branchiocardiac grooves and the interruption of the postcervical groove in hepatic region. In addition to the carapace groove pattern, the slight inflation of ω and χ areas, and the ornamentation made of small tubercles preceded by depressions support the synonymy between 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC51171017FFD40ACAA" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[591,728,885,911]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifera">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC51171017FFD40ACAA" box="[591,728,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. granulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC513BC019CFED6AC8A" authorityName="Secretan" authorityYear="1964" box="[130,334,917,943]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513BC019CFED6AC8A" box="[130,334,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">E. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075EFFC513A501BFFEA9AB8B" blockId="38.[130,777,439,1198]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">
Both ω and χ areas are inflated in 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC512CA01BFFC98ACEA" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[500,768,949,975]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifera">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC512CA01BFFC98ACEA" box="[500,768,949,975]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">Stenodactylina granulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, contrary to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC513C701DFFEFCACCB" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[249,356,980,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC513C701DFFEFCACCB" box="[249,356,980,1007]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5124F01DFFD98ACCB" baseAuthorityName="Moret" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[369,512,980,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delphinensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5124F01DFFD98ACCB" box="[369,512,980,1007]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. delphinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5113201DFFD23ACCB" baseAuthorityName="Van Straelen" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[524,699,980,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deslongchampsi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5113201DFFD23ACCB" box="[524,699,980,1007]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. deslongchampsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC511F901DFFE9DAB2B" authority="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier, 2021" authorityName="Devillez &amp; Charbonnier" authorityYear="2021" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shotoverigiganti" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC511F901DFFE9DAB2B" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. shotoverigiganti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="889B57F6075EFFC5123501FFFEDEAB2A" box="[267,326,1013,1039]" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC5127101FFFE59AB2B" baseAuthorityName="Stenzel" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[335,449,1012,1039]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triglypta">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075EFFC5127101FFFE59AB2B" box="[335,449,1012,1039]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="61">S. triglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075EFFC512C401FFFDF7AB2B" baseAuthorityName="Feldmann &amp; Haggart" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[506,623,1012,1039]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="38" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="walkerae">
